01/06/2003
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The country will likely achieve the status of a functional market economy in the European Commission's 2003 country report, according to Romania's chief negotiator with the EU, Vasile Puscas. At a press conference Saturday (31 May), he noted that Romania's preparations for satisfying EU accession requirements are an ongoing process. He added that the government is making substantial efforts to convince the Union that the country has a functional market economy. (Rompres - 31/05/03)
